  "description": "Fast triage dashboard for container logs shipped by Promtail and stored in Loki, designed to validate that the demo logging pipeline is alive and usable.\n\nWorkflow: start from total log volume and overall log rate to confirm ingestion, then use “Top Services” to identify noisy components. When the error signal is non-zero, pivot to “Errors — Top Services” to attribute the source before drilling into the raw log panel.\n\nFiltering: use the $service variable to scope the investigation to one or more services. For faster browsing, keep the dashboard at 30 minutes and use the Logs panel as the final step once a suspect service is identified.\n\nData source: Loki (Docker container logs via Promtail).\n\nSecurity: logs may contain sensitive operational metadata (hostnames, internal endpoints, user identifiers, tokens in query parameters). Restrict dashboard access and avoid sharing raw log output without redaction.",
